 Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Fielding was born in 1370, in Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Joan Prudhome."},"et":{"1370–":"1370–Surnud","1370–Female":"1370–Surnud","1395–1450":"1395–1450","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1370":"1370","Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England":"Lutterworth, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1370–":"1370–Kuollut","1370–Female":"1370–Kuollut","1395–1450":"1395–1450","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1370":"1370","Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England":"Lutterworth, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1370–":"1370–Décédé","1370–Female":"1370–Décédée","1395–1450":"1395–1450","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1370":"1370","Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England":"Lutterworth, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir William Fielding est né en 1370, à Lutterworth, Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan Prudhome."},"de":{"1370–":"1370–Verstorben","1370–Female":"1370–Verstorben","1395–1450":"1395–1450","1370–Male":"1370–Verstorben","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1370":"1370","Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England":"Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Sir William Fielding wurde 1370 in Lutterworth, Leicestershire, England, United King